		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This research programme will build on initial results generated under a British Council funded collaboration with the Weizmann Institute in Israel.  During this work we have reported the observation of a discrete spatial soliton in a non-linear wave-guide array. The present application will extend this research to carry out a study of discrete non-linear systems.  This project will investigate a range of non-linear phenomena associated with discrete systems.  We will use well qualified non-linearity of AlGaAs to fabricate a range of discrete samples use these to characterise resulting non-linear, localised states.  In particular we will characterise the formation, interaction and polarisation nature of discrete spatial solitons.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
